The paper deals with high-dimensional sparse estimation tasks in a robust setting, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The use of spectral techniques and iterative filtering suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), statistics (cs.ST), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
